#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:6
msgid ""
"Here are some preferences that you may wish to set initially. The full "
"list and explanation of the user preferences are documented in the "
"section :doc:`User Preferences </preferences/index>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:12
msgid "Language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:14
msgid ""
"At :menuselection:`File --> User Preferences --> System`, enable "
"*International Fonts* to choose the *Language* and what to translate from"
" *Interface*, *Tooltips* and *New Data*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:17
msgid "See :ref:`prefs-system-international` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:21
msgid "Input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:23
msgid ""
"If you have a compact keyboard without a separate number pad, enable "
":menuselection:`File --> User Preferences --> Emulate Numpad`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:26
msgid ""
"If you do not have a middle mouse button, you can enable "
":menuselection:`File --> User Preferences --> Emulate 3 Button Mouse`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:29
msgid "See :doc:`Input Preferences </preferences/input>` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:33
msgid "File and Paths"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:35
msgid ""
"At :menuselection:`File --> User Preferences --> File` you can set "
"options such as what external *Image Editor* to use, such as GIMP or "
"Krita, and the Animation Player."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:39
msgid ""
"The :ref:`temp-dir` sets where to store files such as temporary renders "
"and auto-saves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:43
msgid ""
"The ``//`` at the start of each path in Blender means the directory of "
"the currently opened blend-file, used to reference relative paths."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:46
msgid ""
"If you trust the source of your blend-files, you can enable *Auto Run "
"Python Scripts*. This option is meant to protect you from malicious "
"Python scripts that someone can include inside a blend-file. This would "
"not happen by accident, and most users leave this option on to "
"automatically run scripts often used in advanced rigs (such as \"Rigify\""
" that controls the skeleton of a human rig)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing/configuration/introduction.rst:52
msgid "See :doc:`File Preferences </preferences/file>` for details."
msgstr ""

